Metathorax
: metapostnotum (pn 
3
) absent; metatergal setae (mts): 2 fs + 0 or 1 hs on each side. Dorsospiracular setae (dss): 5–8 fs on each side. Dorsal part of metapleural ridge (plr 
3
) absent and without a suspensorial sclerite (ss). Ventral part of metapleural ridge well developed; episternum (eps 
3
) probably unsclerotised; with 3–5 postmetaspiracular setae (eps 
3
s) on either side. Metepimeron (epm 
3
) short or absent. Antemetaspiracular setae (am 
3
s) absent. Metathoracic spiracle (sp 
3
): width of peritreme 20–24 μm; with 1–4 disc-pores on each side. Metasternum (stn 
3
) membranous; anterior metasternal setae (amss): 8–10 setae; posterior metasternal setae (pmss): 4–6 setae.
